what are your thoughts friends? see you in the field! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaludramaderlas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaludram Aderlas</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.fortunecity.com/samslade/shadcon/Images/minisc.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 9:32:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE:Since its Roleplaying prefered....</span><hr size=1> 1.) Personally I find the roleplay tag ridiculous.  I have always found it bad roleplaying as nothing changes on EQ.  You do not see the scars on the body of the old, skilled, warrior or the deep wrinkles of the ancient wizard.  The level indication that /roleplay hides should be considered an indication of this, sadly it seems the slow-witted have spoken once more en masse. &lt;sigh&gt; <br>
<br>
2.)Agreed, yet another ridiculous thing.  Certainly I have been in roleplaying tabletop groups where /ooc was not allowed.  I did not find it fun and left them.  Roleplaying should always be fun, and if one cannot relax occassionally and slip out of character for a moment just to talk about how bad work was or how their car was acting up, fun goes out the window.  Again, the zealots and martyrs of roleplay force people to do as THEY see fit. &lt;sigh&gt;<br>
<br>
3.)Tells are FAR from roleplaying.  I do not recall reading anyhow on Norrath has psionics.  If you want to remove /ooc and force /roleplay, tells should also not exist by the same lack if wisdom.<br>
<br>
4.)Human, Verant's new Common.  They did a great job with this.  They shut the zealots up whilst allowing those not quite as insane a route to actually communicate.  Personally the one thing that was done that I do like is the whole language system.  Kudos to Verant on that one. <br>
<br>
5.)I am adding this.  My last and final beef is about abusive people who play this game.  I am sick and tired of it.  I know plenty of people that switch between roleplaying and non-roleplaying all the time with nary an ill comment between them.  However now we find that those who were abused by the few morons that attacked roleplaying now are abusive.  Are those of you who do this so small and weak in real life to need to get some form of revenge?  Did those who said &quot;look, a loser roleplayer&quot; really hurt your delicate ego that much?  Certainly I could understand if you were all pre-teen, and to those of you that are I apologize as you have not had the chance to build a resilient psyche.  To those of you that are not, shame on you.  You are a disgrace to the human race and you are the same kind of people that derive great pleasure from the pain and suffering of others.  <br>
<br>
I roleplay on occassion in EQ.  When I WISH to roleplay.  I have perhaps once or twice received negative comments, and this is in a year time span.   I simply laughed at these people and moved on.  I did not waste my time being abusive towards them.  In real life I have tabletop roleplayed for over 16 years.  Most of those years I have GMed, and I am told I do so very well.  Does this make me a better roleplayer? No.  Do I care if you roleplay or if you roleplayer better or worse? No.  I do not need such petty and childish things to justify who I am.  I have nothing to prove, I know who I am and what I am.  <br>
<br>
I allow people to ENJOY themselves in whatever way they wish as long as it does me no harm.  I only hope one day those people I see with a chip on their shoulder, abusing non-roleplayers, quite literally grow up.  I hope they find the guidance they need to one day be good members of the human race.  I also only hope I speak for the majority of people, if nay, then this world is surely doomed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uliusadh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liusadh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f75.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/14/01 10:53:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/evermyst/images/chalice.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE:Since its Roleplaying prefered....</span><hr size=1> I agree with all but #4.   <p><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/evermyst/images/liuclose.gif" border="0">
