There are too many components to this game that are not 'realistic', but game related.  For example, you can only grow stronger (even as a healer?!?!) by killing things or being in groups that kill things, unless you want to deliver mail for 60 levels.  Therefore, you cannot just take in the RP ramifacations of the RP tag.  For that matter /who is not a RP command at all.  I can't just think /who in real life and see the name of every person that lives in my apartment complex.  Therefore, /who is a game command... so why put a roleplaying 'realism' on it?<br>
<br>
/shout Is there anyone in zone that can ress?<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
/shout What great druid here could take the time to port me?<br>
<br>
